Rest Operator
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is the output of the following code?
function foo(x, ...y) {
   return x * y.length
}
foo(4,1,2,30);
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Options
This problem has only one correct answer
0
3
12
16
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ANSWER:12
Solution Description
Here, ..y is a rest parameter. Rest parameters are used to transform individual elements into an array and rest operators should be written at the end inside the function declaration. 
So, value 4 is assigned to variable x and the rest (1,2,30) are passed as an array of length 3. So, answer is 12.
